Organ trafficking in Russia has been a growing concern, with doctors accused of illegal kidney removal.
A new law aims to allow local hospitals to perform organ transplants, addressing the shortage issue.
In China, reports reveal unethical practices of harvesting organs from Falungong practitioners.
Meanwhile, in the Philippines, organ donation has become a lucrative business, especially among the poor.
In the US, efforts are being made to incentivize organ donation.
The closure of a kidney transplant program at Kaiser Permanente has raised ethical questions.
Globally, the need for organ donation regulation is emphasized to prevent abuse and ensure ethical practices.
